\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {3}{\ignorespaces  {\bf  a)} ${\xi _{\sf  er}}$ against $e^{\beta J}$ for different values of $v$. The inset shows the slopes $s$ of linear fits of ${\xi _{\sf  er}}$ to $e^{\beta J}$ (drawn as dashed black lines), confirming \textup  {\hbox {\mathsurround \z@ \normalfont  (\ignorespaces \ref  {ler_scaling}\unskip \@@italiccorr )}}. {\bf  b)} Estimates for ${t_{\sf  mem}}$ as a function of $v$, obtained with forward flux sampling. {\bf  c)} ${t_{\sf  mem}}$ plotted against $(\beta J)^2$. {\bf  d)} $E(v) / E(0)$. At low enough temperatures, the energy decreases at large enough $v$. }}{3}{figure.3}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:quantfig}{{3}{3}{{\bf a)} $\ler $ against $e^{\b J}$ for different values of $v$. The inset shows the slopes $s$ of linear fits of $\ler $ to $e^{\b J}$ (drawn as dashed black lines), confirming \eqref {ler_scaling}. {\bf b)} Estimates for $\tmem $ as a function of $v$, obtained with forward flux sampling. {\bf c)} $\tmem $ plotted against $(\b J)^2$. {\bf d)} $E(v) / E(0)$. At low enough temperatures, the energy decreases at large enough $v$}{figure.3}{}}
